      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Family news and details of their health, economic and social status, and migrations are
            discussed in letters to Lydia Lavern Brown Coye Holcomb and to her son, Elmer N. Coye,
            in Ontario County, New York, from Alice Sabina Brown Morgan, Sarah Ann Brown Olmstead,
            and Vesta A. Olmstead, California; Hersalora Catherine Brown Stephenson, Illinois;
            Juliet A. Brown, Sanford Brown, Sarah A. Brown, and Emma A. Brown, Hungerford, Iowa;
            Avery Brown, Elmera Brown Dickinson and Maryett Brown Matteson, Kansas; Otis Gilbert
            Brown, South Dakota; Amelia Brown, Byron Brown, and Carrie A. Brown, Wisconsin; and L.
            DeWitt Brown and S. Alcesta Easton. Also includes later correspondence among the
            following Coye and Holcomb family members: Mrs. Herbert Coye, William Coye, Winifred
            Coye, Adelbert Holcomb, Alice Roderick Holcomb, Elva Wilson, and Howard Wilson; business
            correspondence relating to the Holcomb &amp; Coye farm and apiary; Nathan H. Coye's
            account books (1845-1859); Avery Brown's letter journals sent from Wisconsin to his
            family in Ontario County (1854); Lydia Coye Holcomb's diaries (1867, 1883, 1888-1896);
            Elmer N. Coye's diaries (1869, 1890); newspaper clippings (in part, photocopies); Brown
            family genealogical register; Coye family ledger, 1796-1849; and material related to the
            Wilson family, 1909-1959.</p>
      </scopecontent>
